## Part 9 — Attention Invariants

### 9.1 Invariant Framework

Every invariant is a rule that must hold true for the Attention System to be correct. Invariants are grouped by category.

### Category 1: Identity Invariants (INV-ATT-001 to INV-ATT-005)

| ID | Invariant |
|----|-----------|
| INV-ATT-001 | Every Attention allocation has exactly one unique identity at any time. |
| INV-ATT-002 | Attention identity is immutable once assigned. |
| INV-ATT-003 | Attention identity must be distinct from all other cognitive entity identities (Observation, Memory, Knowledge, Pattern, Evidence, Reasoning, Decision). |
| INV-ATT-004 | An Attention allocation's identity persists across its entire lifecycle (Candidate through Retired). |
| INV-ATT-005 | An identity cannot be reused for a different Attention allocation, even after the original allocation is Retired. |

### Category 2: Lifecycle Invariants (INV-ATT-006 to INV-ATT-020)

| ID | Invariant |
|----|-----------|
| INV-ATT-006 | Every Attention allocation exists in exactly one lifecycle stage at any time. |
| INV-ATT-007 | Lifecycle transitions are monotonic: forward transitions only, no regression (except Deferred → Focused). |
| INV-ATT-008 | Candidate is always the initial stage. Every Attention allocation begins as Candidate. |
| INV-ATT-009 | Only Candidate allocations can be Queued. |
| INV-ATT-010 | Only Queued allocations can become Focused. |
| INV-ATT-011 | Only Focused allocations can become Distributed, Sustained, Interrupted, Deferred, or Completed. |
| INV-ATT-012 | Only Sustained allocations can become Completed (natural completion after sustained processing). |
| INV-ATT-013 | Only Interrupted or Deferred allocations can return to Focused. |
| INV-ATT-014 | Only Expired or Completed allocations can become Archived. |
| INV-ATT-015 | Only Archived allocations can become Retired. |
| INV-ATT-016 | An Attention allocation must exit each stage before entering the next. |
| INV-ATT-017 | An Attention allocation cannot skip intermediate stages (except: Candidate → Retired for noise rejection). |
| INV-ATT-018 | An Attention allocation in Archived or Retired stage is read-only. |
| INV-ATT-019 | An Attention allocation cannot be deleted. Lifecycle ends at Retired. |
| INV-ATT-020 | An Attention allocation in Focused stage must remain uninterrupted for at least its minimum focus duration (except emergency interrption). |

