## Part 12 — Business Examples

### 12.1 Example Framework

Each business example demonstrates a realistic Restaurant OS scenario, showing how Attention is created, allocated, processed, and resolved.

#### Example 1: Inventory Depletion

| Aspect | Detail |
|--------|--------|
| **Scenario** | Tomato inventory drops below threshold during Saturday dinner service. |
| **Trigger** | Inventory Observation exceeds depletion threshold. |
| **Stimulus** | "Tomato inventory at 15% of par, projected to run out in 45 minutes at current consumption rate." |
| **Source** | Inventory Perception channel. |
| **Priority evaluation** | Priority 7 (operational — impacts immediate service). |
| **Urgency evaluation** | Urgency 8 (45 minutes to stockout is urgent). |
| **Value calculation** | Impact: would need to remove items from menu or substitute. Expected value: high (prevent service disruption). |
| **Category** | Operational Attention (primary). Anomaly Attention (secondary — below threshold is anomalous). |
| **Allocation decision** | Admitted to queue above Monitor threshold. Focus Score 5 (requires action but does not require exclusive processing). |
| **Lifecycle** | Candidate → Queued → Focused → Completed (Owner notified, action taken — expedite order or retrieve from backup storage). |
| **Quality assessment** | Relevance: 9 — directly impacted operations. Precision: 8 — correct target. Recall: 10 — no other inventory issues missed. |
| **Outcome** | Owner restocks from cold storage. Service continues uninterrupted. |

#### Example 2: Online Review Spike

| Aspect | Detail |
|--------|--------|
| **Scenario** | Restaurant receives five 1-star reviews on a single platform within 2 hours. |
| **Trigger** | Pattern detects review rate anomaly (5x normal negative review rate). |
| **Stimulus** | "Negative review rate spike detected. 5 reviews in 2 hours. Common complaint: service wait times." |
| **Source** | External Perception channel (review platform monitoring). |
| **Priority evaluation** | Priority 9 (strategic — online reputation has long-term impact). |
| **Urgency evaluation** | Urgency 7 (reviews are visible immediately). |
| **Value calculation** | Impact: reputation damage, reduced future customers. Expected value: high — identify root cause and respond. |
| **Category** | Strategic Attention (primary). Anomaly Attention (secondary). |
| **Allocation decision** | Admitted above Evaluate threshold. Focus Score 7 (requires investigation, multiple data sources). |
| **Lifecycle** | Candidate → Queued → Focused → Distributed (cross-reference with POS data, shift schedule) → Sustained → Completed. |
| **Quality assessment** | Relevance: 10 — genuine reputation threat. Precision: 9 — correctly identified review spike. Recall: 10 — no other reputation issues. |
| **Outcome** | System identifies understaffing during peak hours. Recommends schedule adjustment. Owner approves. |

#### Example 3: Health Inspection Notice

| Aspect | Detail |
|--------|--------|
| **Scenario** | Health department schedules an inspection for next week. |
| **Trigger** | External calendar event detected. |
| **Stimulus** | "Health inspection scheduled: Wednesday, 10 AM. Standard inspection with 24-hour notice." |
| **Source** | External scheduler integration. |
| **Priority evaluation** | Priority 10 (emergency — health inspection affects license). |
| **Urgency evaluation** | Urgency 6 (one week away — time to prepare). |
| **Value calculation** | Impact: critical — license could be affected. Expected value: very high — preparation prevents violations. |
| **Category** | Emergency Attention (primary). Strategic Attention (secondary — preparation plan). |
| **Allocation decision** | Admitted at Interrupt threshold. Focus Score 9 (preparation requires sustained effort). |
| **Lifecycle** | Candidate → Queued → Focused (current processing interrupted) → Sustained (preparation plan developed) → Distributed (tasks assigned across systems) → Completed. |
| **Quality assessment** | Relevance: 10. Precision: 10. Recall: 9 (no other compliance issues discovered). |
| **Outcome** | System generates preparation checklist. Schedules pre-inspection self-audit. Owner approves plan. |

#### Example 4: Owner Goal Question

| Aspect | Detail |
|--------|--------|
| **Scenario** | Owner asks: "How are we tracking against this month's revenue target?" |
| **Trigger** | Owner voice command or text input. |
| **Stimulus** | "Owner query: revenue target progress." |
| **Source** | Owner communication channel. |
| **Priority evaluation** | Priority 9 (Owner — override). |
| **Urgency evaluation** | Urgency 5 (Owner expects timely response). |
